import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['values'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['values'].median()))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of values in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['width'] = pd.to_numeric(data['width'], errors='coerce')
    data['height'] = pd.to_numeric(data['height'], errors='coerce')
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='width', y='height')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between width and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['width'] = pd.to_numeric(data['width'], errors='coerce')
    data['height'] = pd.to_numeric(data['height'], errors='coerce')
    avg_width = data['width'].mean()
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=['Average Width', 'Average Height'], y=[avg_width, avg_height], ax=ax)
    ax.axhline(avg_width, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Width: {avg_width:.2f}')
    ax.axhline(avg_height, color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average width and height in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
